{
  "text": "TYLCCNV is a monopartite begomovirus associated with the Tomato yellow leaf curl China betasatellite (TYLCCNB), which is required by the virus to induce typical disease symptoms in host plants . In common with all betasatellites, TYLCCNB encodes a single protein known as bC1 that is a pathogenicity factor [CITATION_1] , a suppressor of both PTGS [CITATION_2] and TGS (Yang et al., 2011b) , and interferes with host auxin and jasmonate signalling pathways [CITATION_3] . The study described here has characterized a distinct, naturally occurring recombinant monopartite begomovirus originating from Yunnan, China. This virus shows the highest levels of nucleotide sequence identity with TYLCCNV, with most of the sequence variation between the two viruses occurring in the C4 gene. The C4 protein of the recombinant virus is shown to be multifunctional, acting as a pathogenicity factor and a suppressor of both PTGS and TGS. These findings highlight the functional equivalence between the C4 of the recombinant virus and bC1.",
